.:: Puzzle 3x5-Level-4-4::.
5 different games are played: scrabble, chess, backgammon, monopoly, domino
The people grow 5 different varities of flowers: begonia, iris, amaryllis, aconite, balloon-flower
The people use 5 different means of transport: boat, car, subway, taxi, van
 1. the person driving the car is on the left or right of the person who growsamaryllis##3
 2. the person driving the subway is on the left or right of the person driving the van##3
 3. the person driving the car is on the left or right of the person playing backgammon##3
 4. the person who growsamaryllis is on the left or right of the person who growsiris##3
 5. the person playing chess is on the far right##1
 6. the person who growsiris is on the left or right of the person playing scrabble##3
 7. the person driving the boat is on the right of the person driving the car##1
 8. the person who growsiris is on the left of the person driving the taxi##1
 9. the person who growsballoon-flower is in an even position##4
10. the person driving the van is in an odd position##4
11. the person playing scrabble is on the far left or far right##3
12. the person who growsaconite is on the left of the person playing domino##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |   2    |    3    |   4    |    5    |
| Game   | scrabble     | domino    | backgammon  | monopoly | chess |
| Flower           | aconite | iris    | amaryllis | balloon-flower  | begonia    |
| Transport     | van      | subway | taxi    | car    | boat    |

