.:: Puzzle 3x5-Level-4-5::.
5 different games are played: billiard, canasta, mah-jongg, whist, go
House: tower, colonial, cottage, farmhouse, palace
The people use 5 different means of transport: airplane, scooter, ship, snowmobile, train
 1. the person driving the scooter is the person playing go##1
 2. the person driving the train is on the left or right of the person playing mah-jongg##3
 3. the person driving the ship is in an even position##4
 4. the person playing go is the farmhouse house##1
 5. the person driving the snowmobile is between the person driving the airplane and the person playing go##2
 6. the person playing canasta is in the middle##1
 7. the tower house is on the left of the colonial house##1
 8. the person driving the airplane is on the right of the cottage house##1
 9. the palace house is on the far right##1
10. the cottage house is on the left of the person driving the airplane##1
11. the person playing whist is the palace house##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |     2      |    3     |     4     |    5    |
| Game   | go    | billiard        | canasta    | mah-jongg      | whist  |
| House   | farmhouse | cottage    | tower | colonial | palace |
| Transport     | scooter   | snowmobile | airplane | ship      | train   |

